<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Threatens Milosevic with "Little Time Left" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- British Defense Secretary George
Robertson on Tuesday warned Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic
that there was "very little time left" to resolve the rapidly
escalating crisis over Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
"President Milosevic has very little time left now. But he
should in that remaining time listen carefully to the message that
has been given -- pull back, stop the violence and sign up to a
political agreement," Robertson was quoted by Reuters as saying.
</P>
<P>
"If military action has to be taken, then it will be his
responsibility" and all NATO members were united, according to
Robertson, speaking after talks with Greek Defense Minister
Apostolos-Athanassios Tsohatzopoulos.
</P>
<P>
"There is a humanitarian catastrophe looming if the violence
does not stop," Robertson said. "We are absolutely determined that
the violence and misery being inflicted on the ordinary people of
Kosovo must stop."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
