<DOCNO> XIE19990324.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Stands Ready to Strike Yugoslavia: Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said on Tuesday that Britain stood ready with its NATO allies to
take military action against Yugoslavia if there is no resolution
to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
"Britain stands ready with our NATO allies to take military
action," Blair said during a speech in the parliament.
</P>
<P>
There was "little cause to be optimistic" about the outcome of
latest attempts in Belgrade to persuade Yugoslav President
Slobodan Milosevic to accept a peace deal, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said military action would be taken
primarily to avoid what he described as a humanitarian disaster in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
There were more than 250,000 people homeless in Kosovo as a
result of repression by Serb forces, he said.
</P>
<P>
To walk away from the situation now "would destroy NATO's
credibility," he told the parliament.  
</P>
</TEXT>
