<HEADLINE> Antic Rejoins Atletico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Raddy Antic, the most successful
coach in the history of Spanish giants Atletico Madrid, has agreed
to rejoin the first division side, local reports said here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The former Yugoslav international will take over from Spain's
Carlos Sanchez Aguiar, a temporary replacement who resigned
following Atletico's 2-0 defeat on Sunday against Alaves.
</P>
<P>
Antic coached Atletico until 1997 and in 1996 led them to the
first Spanish Championship and Cup double in the history of the
club. Atletico are presently a lowly 12th in the Spanish league
table. 
</P>
</TEXT>
