<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Plant 156 Million Trees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's Ministry of
Agriculture announced Tuesday that it has finalized preparations
to plant 156 million tree-seedlings on 78,000 hectares of land
across the country during the coming big rainy season which starts
in June and ends in September.
</P>
<P>
Million Bekele, leader of the forest and wildlife technology
control team under the ministry, told local press that over 62
million birr (about 7.9 million U.S. dollars) is needed to carry
out the transplantation.
</P>
<P>
A total of 95 percent of the rural people in the country depend
on fuel wood as a source of energy, he said, adding that "the
ever-increasing depletion of forests is aggravating the looming
threat of desertification."
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's forested area, which was 40 percent of the land mass
50 years ago, has been reduced to a mere 2.5 percent in recent
years. To reverse the trend of deforestation, the Ethiopian
government has taken strict control measures on tree-felling. The
new policy envisaged the development of forest over 8,000 hectares
of land annually during the past five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
