<HEADLINE> Ukraine Insists on Political Settlement of Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine maintains its position on
the Kosovo issue and insists on a settlement of armed conflict in
the region through peaceful means, First Deputy Foreign Minister
Yevgeni Bersheda said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Bersheda noted that any
military action against Yugoslavia should be authorized by the U.N.
Security Council.
</P>
<P>
He said the Ukrainian government was taking steps to evacuate
Ukrainian citizens from Yugoslavia. But he also pointed out that
it was still too early to talk about the question of evacuation.
</P>
<P>
Bersheda said that considering the unpredictability of the
situation in Yugoslavia, the ministry had advised the Ukrainian
nationals not to head for the troubled region. Those currently
living there had been reminded to keep a close watch on
developments and pay attention to their safety. 
</P>
</TEXT>
