<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Troops on Alert in North Caucasus Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Russia's interior troops stationed
in the North Caucasus Region have entered a state of alert since
the March 19 bomb blast which killed more than 50 people, Pavel
Maslov, commander of the interior troops announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Troops have begun patrolling the streets, searching for
explosive devices and protecting densely-populated sites,
important facilities, schools and hospitals, Maslov said.
</P>
<P>
Also on Thursday, Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Interior
Minister Sergei Stepashin discussed ways to stabilize the North
Caucasus Region during their working meeting, according to the
president's press secretary, Dmitri Yakushkin.
</P>
<P>
Stepashin briefed the president about the investigation of the
explosion, and Yeltsin stressed that measures must be taken to
ease the tension in the North Caucasus Region.
</P>
<P>
The explosion on March 19 in Vladikavkaz, the regional capital
near the independence-seeking Chechnya, killed 53 people and
injured 101 others.
</P>
<P>
Stepashin went to the scene on orders from Yeltsin to
investigate the blast shortly after it happened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
