<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Calls for Restraint on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
Tuesday made a strong appeal to all sides involved in the Kosovo
issue to exercise restraint, show patience and adopt a flexible
attitude.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with Italian Prime Minister Massimo D'Alema, Jiang
said that all sides concerned should continue to negotiate a
proper and just solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said that the latest developments of the
Kosovo issue had caused concern and anxiety among peace-loving
people all over the world.
</P>
<P>
The people living in Kosovo yearned for peace and the Kosovo
issue is an internal issue of Yugoslavia, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China maintained that the sovereignty and territorial integrity
of Yugoslavia should be respected and the Kosovo issue should be
resolved through political dialogue, taking due consideration to
ensure the rights of various ethnic groups there, the Chinese
president said.
</P>
<P>
D'Alema briefed Jiang on the situation in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The Italian premier said that Italy was deeply concerned over
the latest developments in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country would work hard to help ensure a peace
agreement is reached. 
</P>
</TEXT>
