<HEADLINE> Election Campaign Kicks Off in Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Malawi Electoral Commission
Wednesday announced the commencement of political campaigning for
the country's second multi-party presidential and parliamentary
elections for 1999.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued Wednesday by the commission's press
officer Symon Kambalame said the campaigning period lasts two
months according to Section 57 of the Parliamentary and
Presidential Act, 1993.
</P>
<P>
Campaigning closes on May 23, at 6:00 a.m., 48 hours before the
opening of the poll on May 25.
</P>
<P>
The commission has since ordered that no person shall hold a
campaign meeting in or within the premises of military units or
police stations, public institutions and work places during normal
working hours, and educational institutions during periods of
classes.
</P>
<P>
The act, the press release said, also prohibits campaigning in
public places without prior notification to police and the
district commissioner. 
