<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Rules Out Participation in Military Action Against Serbia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria will not join military
action against Yugoslavia and was facing no threats, President
Peter Stoyanov said on National Radio Wednesday morning after NATO
Secretary-General Javier Solana authorized the start of military
action.
</P>
<P>
"Bulgaria's position on the conflict in Kosovo remains
unchanged: this country will not join military action, if any,
against neighboring Yugoslavia," Stoyanov said.
</P>
<P>
