Council on National Security. "Nothing has changed since my
statement late last night," he said, adding that he was closely
following developments and the council would be immediately
convened if necessary. This, however, should not create needless
tension in his opinion.
</P>
<P>
Stoyanov also indicated that he would not cancel his trip to
the Germany city of Leipzig for the opening of a book fair. "If I
don't go, this might be seen as an indication of anxiety and
tension," he explained.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in parliament on Wednesday, the leader of the
opposition Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP) strongly opposed any
military action without a U.N. mandate.
</P>
<P>
