Security with the President and a separate extraordinary sitting
of the National Assembly on the crisis in Kosovo to hear Prime
Minister Ivan Kostov.
</P>
<P>
"We categorically oppose any military operations unsanctioned
by the UN Security Council," Purvanov said.
</P>
<P>
The Floor Leader of the ruling Union of Democratic Forces
Ekaterina Mihailova called on politicians to treat the situation
calmly and responsibly and not to politicize the matter. "All
institutions in the country are ready to react if necessary," she
said. The Socialists greeted this statement by banging on the
desks in the debating chamber.
</P>
<P>
When the National Assembly Chairman Yordan Sokolov refused to
put to the vote the Socialists' motion for a parliamentary debate
on the Kosovo crisis, the Socialist MPs walked out of the sitting
in protest. 
