<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cold Front Kills One in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A strong cold front that has
lingered in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in
the past week has so far killed one person and caused the illness
of a further 104 in Altay Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
Over 2,000 heads of cattle and sheep also died in the freezing
cold, while over 800 more livestock were slaughtered by wolves.
</P>
<P>
The cold front has come from Siberia in Russia, which has made
the already sub-zero temperatures in the area even colder, with
the lowest at over 30 degrees centigrade below zero.
</P>
<P>
Local government officials and troops have rushed to the rescue.
</P>
<P>
The area suffered heavy casualties and economic losses from
devastating snowstorms last year, according to local officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
