<HEADLINE> EU Leaders Agree Prodi As EU Commission Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) leaders agreed
here at their summit meeting on Wednesday to nominate former
Italian prime minister Romano Prodi as new president of the
European Commission, the EU's executive branch, German Chancellor
Gerhard Schroeder told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Germany is holding the rotating EU presidency for the first
half of this year. Schroeder said on behalf of the EU leaders that
the European Council has shown its unrestricted capability to act,
adding that Prodi stood for both reform and integrity in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The current EU president said this will raise trust in the
ability of European institutions to do business and thus create
more confidence in the power of Europe.
</P>
<P>
Shroeder also said the new European Commission president should
serve a full five-year term, and that the European leaders hoped
Mr. Prodi could start his mandate on April 1. 
</P>
