<HEADLINE> Nepali Government Bans Strikes in 3 Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 24 (Xinhua) -- In an attempt to force the
pilots of the national flag carrier to end their 10-day strike,
the Nepalese government Wednesday banned strikes in the sectors of
communication, transportation and defense, Radio Nepal said.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet made the decision in accordance with related acts
and in view of the upcoming general elections, it said.
</P>
<P>
The pilots of the Royal Nepal Airlines Corporation have been
grounding all the domestic and international flights for the past
10 days because the management has not fulfilled their demand for
cancellation of an agreement to lease Boeing 757 plane from the
China Southwest Airlines.
</P>
<P>
They have called for lease-purchasing another aircraft. The
management, however, does not agree.
</P>
<P>
The strike has come under criticism from the private sector and
the tourism sector in the country.
</P>
<P>
The election to the House of Representatives is scheduled for
May 3 and May 17. 
