<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Major Wood Pulp Enterprise in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China signed an
agreement here today to provide a loan of 175 million US dollars
to Shandong Rizhao Wood Pulp Co. Ltd., initiating the country's
largest paper-making production project.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of 2.9 billion yuan (349 million US
dollars), the enterprise in Rizhao City, Shandong Province, will
have an annual production capacity of 170,000 tons of pulp for the
paper-making industry.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China imports at least 600,000 tons of
wood pulp every year, said a local official, the operation of this
company will greatly relieve the domestic shortage.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated the company will need 850,000 cubic meters of
wood as raw materials annually, he said, adding that the company
has signed import contracts with timber suppliers in Chile,
Venezuela, Australia and Russia. 
</P>
