<HEADLINE> India Reiterates Stand on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government Wednesday
reiterated its stand on the Kosovo issue, saying the sovereignty
and territorial integrity of the international border of
Yugoslavia are inviolable.
</P>
<P>
"We are of the firm conviction that the resolution of this
crisis can only be through peaceful means, through consultation
and dialogue, and not through either confrontation or any military
action, unilateral or otherwise," an official spokesman said in a
statement released here.
</P>
<P>
"In this regard we wish to reaffirm commitments to the U.N.
Charter, which clearly stipulates that no enforcement actions
shall be undertaken under regional arrangements without the
authorization of the Security Council," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"The government of India has closely been following
developments in Kosovo," it said. 
