<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang's Visit Hailed by Italian News Media </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MILAN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Italian news media have fully
covered Chinese President Jiang Zemin's ongoing state visit to
Italy and hailed it as an "event of historic significance in the
bilateral relationship".
</P>
<P>
A front page editorial of the local Chinese-language newspaper,
Xinhua Times, said that the Italian president, government and
parties at large have attached great importance to the visit,
which was also welcomed by people from the economic and trade,
scientific and technological, cultural and educational and the
news sectors, particularly by Chinese people residing in Italy.
</P>
<P>
The editorial, entitled "Historic Visit Geared Toward the New
Century", pointed out that a tendency towards multi-polarization
was developing throughout the world. It said that strengthening
contact and cooperation between China and Italy complied with the
fundamental interests of the two peoples, which would be
beneficial to international peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
A front page article in an influential national newspaper,
Republica, predicted the second day after Jiang's arrival that his
three-nation European visit would "surely" be a success, as almost
all the leaders of Western countries have successful talks with
Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The article said, "Jiang, who is cordial, natural and humorous,
is the symbol and front runner of the new generation of the
Chinese leadership".
</P>
<P>
It explained that the reason China had won respect from the
rest of the world in the past year and a half was that it had kept
stable the value of its currency during the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time the Chinese government had to face a
severe international crisis, together with major Western countries
with the spirit of cooperation and "partnership", it said.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper commented that it was "not an easily made
decision for Chinese leaders, and China has paid big price for it".
</P>
<P>
Commenting on Jiang's talks with his Italian counterpart Oscar
Luigi Scalfaro, the national newspaper, Stampa, noted in an
article Tuesday that taking Italy as the first leg of his three-
nation European tour fully demonstrated that China paid great
attention to the development of its relationship with Italy.
</P>
<P>
Another national newspaper, Corriere della Sera, said Wednesday
in a report on Jiang's meeting with Italian Prime Minister Massimo
D'Alema that China's determination to enter into the world
economic system deserved applause.
</P>
<P>
The national newspaper, il Giornale, said on the same day that
Italy was very willing to develop relations with China, and as a
member of the European Union and G7, it would make active efforts
to accelerate the process.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper pointed out that Jiang's visit, especially his
extensive contact with Italian entrepreneurs, would provide
possibilities for enterprises in both countries to establish a
more extensive cooperative relationship of mutual benefit,
especially for cooperation between small and medium-sized
enterprises, in which Italy had achieved some success.
</P>
<P>
Almost all of the Italian new media that have covered Jiang's
visit have mentioned the point that China and Italy have shared
common or similar views on such major international issues as the
Kosovo and Iraq crises and the reform of the Security Council of
the United Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
