<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index Loses 74.81 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday lost 74.81 points to
3,682.69 as against Tuesday's close of 3,757.5.
</P>
<P>
The national index also lost 33.57 points to 1,619.85 as
against the previous close of 1,653.42.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar indexes were quoted down at 373.93
and 146.83 compared with the last close of 380.81 and 149.57
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities crashed in the wake of heavy unloading by operators
due to strong speculation that some big operators were asked to
square up their long outstanding positions on the BSE market
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Operators were also worried about the high outstanding
positions at the Calcutta Stock Exchange. 
