<HEADLINE> Overseas-funded Enterprises Combine Assets in North China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The CTS (Tianjin) Electronics
Company Ltd. went into operation today in Tianjin Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The new company was previously a branch of the Motorola Company
of the United States.
</P>
<P>
This is an indication of an increasing trend to combine assets
among local overseas-funded enterprises in the Tianjin Development
Zone.
</P>
<P>
The 100-year old US-based CTS Company took a stake in Motorola
by buying the branch for 150 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Joseph P. Walker, CTS president, said that his company will
continue its close cooperation with the Motorola Company and he is
confident that this combining of assets will be successful.
</P>
<P>
CTS mainly produces electronic components such as filters and
other special parts for the telecommunications, computer and
automobile industries. Its branch in Tianjin provides components
for mobile telephone manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Motorola is the largest and the most successful American
company in China. Its production value ranks second among overseas-
funded companies in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
