<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks suffered big
losses across the board to close below the 11,000-point level
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip Hang Seng Index declined 329.67 points, or 2.99
percent, to close at 10,711.34.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover was 5.568 billion HK dollars (713 million
U.S. dollars), 825 million HK dollars (105 million U.S. dollars)
more than Tuesday's 4.743 billion HK dollars (608 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The banking shares lost 494.59 points, or 2.97 percent, to
close at 16,157.41, while utilities, properties and commerce and
industry lost 2.85 percent, 3.15 percent and 3.00 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
