<HEADLINE> Over Half HKIFA Members Plan to Join MPF Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey shows that at
least half of the member fund companies of the Hong Kong
Investment Funds Association (HKIFA) plan to participate in the
Mandatory Provident Fund (MPF) market.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the survey conducted by the HKIFA in February
among member fund companies "is to provide insight into the
positioning of the fund management industry in the MPF market, as
well as the role that fund managers will assume in this market,"
HKIFA Chairman Desmond Chan said.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 50 member fund companies, 46 companies responded to
the survey, representing a response rate of 92 percent. And of
these 46 responding companies, 25 companies indicate they will
participate in the MPF market.
</P>
<P>
The 25 companies all will offer investment management services,
which represent their core business.
</P>
<P>
As for the types of investment management products to be
offered, 13 companies indicate they will offer master trusts and
15 companies say they will offer underlying funds.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 19 companies indicate they will set up segregated
funds or offer approved MPF products for employer-sponsored
schemes.
</P>
<P>
"As the survey indicates, most fund managers would be focusing
on providing investment management services. They would work
closely with trustees, banks, insurance companies and investment
consultants which will play an important role in administration
and distribution," Chan said.
</P>
<P>
The HKIFA consists of 50 fund management companies as full
members. They manage assets totaling about 100 billion U.S.
dollars of SFC-authorized unit trusts and mutual funds.
</P>
<P>
It also has 45 associates, including trustees, lawyers and
other professionals who are involved in the creation and
administration of funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
