<HEADLINE> O'Neill Ties Record with 33rd National Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Olympic 200-meter butterfly
champion Susie O'Neill equals Frank Beaurepaire's record of 33
national swimming titles when she won the event at the Australian
national championships in Brisbane on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
She clocked two minutes, 7.35 seconds, the fastest ever time
recorded in Australia, to beat Petria Thomas.
</P>
<P>
The reigning Olympic, world, Commonwealth and Pan Pacific
champion maintained a four and a half years unbeaten streak in the
event. She has not been beaten in a 50 meters pool since she won
bronze at the world championships in Rome in 1994. 
