<HEADLINE> China's Airlines Continuing Growth Over Next 20 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- China's airlines are expected to
maintain an annual growth rate of 8.1 percent over the next 20
years, compared to the world's average of 4.9 percent, according
to Boeing estimates.
</P>
<P>
During that period China's airlines are expected to purchase 1,
800 jetliners valued at 125 billion U.S. dollars, making China the
world's second largest commercial aviation market, after the U.S.
</P>
<P>
Jim Klein, the director of international public relations and
advertising for Boeing's commercial airplane division, during a
recent visit to China, pointed to the brilliant achievements in
cooperation between China and Boeing over the past 28 years.
</P>
<P>
Chinese airlines have 477 jetliners, 324 of which are Boeing
products. In the past five years, Boeing has put hundreds of
millions of dollars into training and equipment to help Chinese
airlines improve flight safety and efficiency. More than 4,300
flight and maintenance personnel have been trained by Boeing.
</P>
<P>
Klein said that key parts made in China have been installed on
more than 3,100 Boeing jetliners that are in service worldwide.
Chinese manufacturers have also participated in parts design and
manufacturing for the next generation of 737s, he says and
expressed confidence in the rapid growth of China's economy in the
future.
</P>
<P>
He said that the annual growth rate of China's GDP was 3.5
times that of North America and Europe for the past 23 years, and
in the next 20 years, China will become the fastest growing region
in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
