<HEADLINE> Foreign Funds Helping North Central China's Forestry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region has brought in 19.3 million US dollars in foreign funds to
develop its forestry in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The funds have come from foreign government, international
institutions, and nongovernmental organizations and have been used
to bring in a dozen better species of trees and advanced
irrigation technology, local authorities say.
</P>
<P>
A Sino-Japanese forest protection plan that received state
approval at the end of last year is intended to kill plant
diseases and insect pests in local forests and to improve the
ecology.
</P>
<P>
A team of at least 270 people from 4 countries has visited the
region for forestry studies and academic exchanges in the last
year. 
