<HEADLINE> Tax System Expands Computer Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- China's taxation departments used
computerized management and supervision systems to monitor some 16.
78 million Chinese taxpayers during 1998, according to a recent
edition of China Taxation News.
</P>
<P>
The system was used to collect taxes totaling 593.3 billion yuan
in 1998, or 69.4 percent of total industrial and commercial tax
revenues nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Taxation departments nationwide were equipped with 157,000
personal computers by the end of 1998, up 28 percent from the 1997
figure.
</P>
<P>
However, only 28,727 technicians were involved in managing and
operating the system.  
</P>
