<HEADLINE> New Expressway In Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction on a new expressway
from Jinzhou to Fuxin in northeast China's Liaoning Province will
start after getting approval from state departments.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning is the leading heavy industry base of China and
Jinzhou and Fuxin are two major industrial hubs of the province.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, work on the projected 118-km.
expressway's design, land acquisition, and resettlement will be
finished this year.
</P>
<P>
The expressway is expected to be finished in 2001, by then it
will connect up with 3 national highways going to Hebei, Inner
Mongolia, and areas south of the Great Wall. It is expected to
help the economic development of western Liaoning, with the city
of Jinzhou at the center.
</P>
<P>
By 1998, China had 6,258 km. of expressways in service. 
</P>
