<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Looting of Ancient Treasures Continuing in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 24 (Xinhua) -- More than half of the nation's
invaluable art treasures have been stolen since 1986, despite
increased efforts to stop the thefts, according to a government
conservationist.
</P>
<P>
"They have vanished or been damaged as a result of theft or
warfare," an official of the Angkor Conservation Department was
quoted by the Cambodia Daily as saying.
</P>
<P>
"To my knowledge, looting is not decreasing. Looters will wait
for their chance and take any opportunity whenever authorities are
careless,"
the official said.
</P>
<P>
The thefts of statues and art treasures have slowed in recent
years thanks in part to the Heritage Police, set up with the help
of the international community in 1994, and the government's
measures. But the looting was still going on and getting seriously
these days.
</P>
<P>
In February, a priceless piece of a 12th-century relief was
stolen from the Banteay Thom temple in Siem Reap. Looters used
hammers and chisels to cut the 0.7-meter-long, one-meter-wide
relief from the temple's pillars.
</P>
<P>
In January, Thai police seized 117 ancient Cambodian sculptures
in the border province of Sa Kaeo, some 250 km east of Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Angkok, the heart of the Khmer empire dating back to the 7th
century and home to 273 of Hindu and Buddhist monuments, has
always been prey to thieves who sell their stolen wares mostly to
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Decades of civil war have also caused widespread damage to
temple sites around the country, and many of the looted sites were
damaged during fighting and have not yet been repaired.
</P>
<P>
Military Police Deputy Commander Prak Chanthoeun said tougher
action must be taken to stop the thefts of the treasures and save
the national heritage.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, special units have been created to investigate
thefts and police have been instructed in many areas to keep a
close eye on possible targets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990324.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
