<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Israeli Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Israeli newspapers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Some 400,000 public sector workers of Israel are to launch a
general strike on Wednesday, which is expected to severely disrupt
essential services of the country. The strike expansion came after
the last-ditch negotiations between the Finance Ministry and the
Labor Union broke down Tuesday night.
</P>
