<HEADLINE> China Attractive To Asia-Pacific Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey has shown that
China is the most attractive place for investors in the Asia-
Pacific Region, and Hong Kong and Singapore are their next choice.
</P>
<P>
The survey by the China Entrepreneur Survey Network found that
95.2 percent showed confidence for investing in China and 34.3
percent said they were "extremely confident".
</P>
<P>
Most of those surveyed said they thought there is still a great
deal of potential in China for overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Of those surveyed, 73 percent have plans for at least 5 years
of business in China and 70 percent have plans for at least ten
years in China.
</P>
<P>
Most surveyed showed satisfaction with energy, water, land, and
office building supplies and say they are especially satisfied
with the relatively plentiful supply of cheap labor.
</P>
<P>
However, 34.7 percent of those surveyed complained that the
current job market in China doesn't meet their demands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
