<HEADLINE> Philippine Army, Muslim Rebels Trade Mortar Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Sporadic exchanges of mortar fire
erupted anew between government forces of the Philippines and
Muslim rebels in the southern province of Sultan Kudarat early
this week, a military report said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The military report sent to the Philippine armed forces said
the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rebels struck two days in
a row, firing 10 rounds of 60mm mortar shells on several army
positions in the province last Sunday and Monday.
</P>
<P>
None of the mortar shells hit their targets, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Army soldiers returned fire, delivering nine rounds of 81mm
mortar on the MILF, the report said.
</P>
<P>
No casualty was reported on both sides, it said.
</P>
<P>
In another southern province of Basilan, an army company fought
two separate gunbattles with rebels believed to be members of an
extremist Muslim group last Monday.
</P>
<P>
One army soldier was wounded, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The company is composed of former guerrillas of the Moro
National Liberation Front recently integrated into the army, it
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
