<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Turkish newspapers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkey's Police General Director Necati Bilican announced
Tuesday three suspected terrorists have been caught in connection
with an arson attack on "Blue Market" shopping mall in Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
On March 13, 13 people were killed and six other injured in the
arson attack in the market, which caused a great panic in
Istanbul, the largest city of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- Administrators of the pro-Kurdish Med-TV based in Britain
are trying to move the TV station to Cyprus after British
Independent Television Commission stopped it broadcasting for 21
days, citing its encouragement of anti-Turkey terrorist acts by
supporters of Abdullah Ocalan, leader of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
Daily News:
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Parliament Speaker Hikmet Cetin said a bright era
has arrived for the Turkish-Syrian relations following the
two-day talks on economic issues between Turkish deputy Prime
Minister Hikmet Ulugbay and Syrian deputy Prime Minister Salim
Yassin, who arrived in Ankara on Monday for a two-day visit to
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Cetin said Syria is the country with the longest border with
Turkey and therefore relations with Syria are very important for
Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
