<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Of China Extending Credit To More Customers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) is
providing credit to more than 70,000 customers via a computer
network.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman was quoted in today's Economic Daily as saying
that giving credit to enterprises helps prevent financial risks
and irregularities.
</P>
<P>
The amount of a bank loan to the company depends on its credit
standing, to put a stop to past practices where a company could
swindle the bank out of more loan money by applying to various
bank branches.
</P>
<P>
BOC has developed a credit system in accordance with
international standards and has provided credit under the new
system to 40 major groups with overseas subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
It has 554 branches overseas and had profits of more than 3.2
billion yuan (386 million U.S. dollars) last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
