<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Embassy Gives Press Conference in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Kosovo will never be allowed to
be separated from Yugoslavia, said Yugoslav ambassador to China
Slobodan Unkovic at a press conference exclusively for Chinese
press here today.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia will never allow North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) troops to enter Kosovo for the so-called supervision, and
will never accept any provision in any document to effect Kosovo
as a third Yugoslav republic, the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador highly valued China's principled stand on the
issue, saying he believed China, along with other peace-loving
nations, would make efforts to stop the looming military action
against his country.
</P>
<P>
At the press time, the press conference is still going on.
</P>
<P>
NATO Secretary-General Javier Solana Tuesday authorized NATO
military forces to launch air strikes against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Qin Huasun, the Chinese permanent representative to the UN.,
said Tuesday that any military action against Yugoslavia without
the authorization of the UN. Security Council will be a severe
violation of the UN. Charter and the established principles of
international law and unacceptable by international community.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday, Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said
that China strongly appeals to relevant parties to settle the
issue by continuing to hold negotiations in an appropriate and
just manner through exercising restraint and adopting a patient
and flexible attitude.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government holds that the Kosovo
issue is an internal affair of Yugoslavia and should be resolved
politically through dialogues on the basis of respecting the
sovereignty and territorial integrity of Yugoslavia and
safeguarding the legitimate rights and interests of various
ethnic groups in the Kosovo region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
