<HEADLINE> NATO Strikes to Begin Shortly: British PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said on Wednesday that NATO forces were ready to act against
Yugoslavia over Kosovo and military strikes would begin very
shortly.
</P>
<P>
"We are resolved to act now ... It's plain that action will
begin in the not too distant future," Blair said in an interview
with BBC radio from a meeting of European Union leaders in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
"Now we are left with no other alternative than to take
military action. We have to see it through all the way," said the
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
But he declined to say how long the action would take.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, NATO Secretary-General Javier Solana told reporters
that he had authorized the NATO forces to take military actions
against Yugoslavia after U.S. envoy Richard Holbrooke failed in
his last-ditch effort to persuade Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic to accept the agreement on the Kosovo issue. 
</P>
