<HEADLINE> Lijiaxia Hydropower Station Nearing Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Lijiaxia
Hydropower Station, the third and largest facility of its kind on
the upper reaches of the Yellow river, is nearing completion.
</P>
<P>
The construction project was initiated in 1987 and three
generating units are currently in operation, with the fourth unit
expected to go online in September.
</P>
<P>
The station, located at the juncture of Jianzha and Hualong
counties in northwest China's Qinghai Province, will have a
designed annual generating capacity of 5.9 billion kwh.
</P>
<P>
Major work on the dam is located at an elevation of 2,185
meters above sea level. The whole dam project has so far consumed
a total of 1.52 million cu.m. of concrete.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
