<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russell Tips the Balance as Utah Squeezes by Miami </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Bryon Russell played like a
chip off the old Jordan when he buried a winning three-pointer to
help the Utah Jazz escape with a 84-81 victory over Maimi Heat on
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
In Salt Lake, Russell drained the long jumper for his fourth 3-
pointer of the night after Jazz guard John Stockton drove to the
foul line and handed off to him on the right wing.
</P>
<P>
"I want to hit the winning shot in the championship game," said
Russell, who was victimised by Michael Jordan on the championship
shot last year.
</P>
<P>
"To hit a game-winning shot like tonight doesn't mean a thing,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Miami won most of the physical battles in the thriller as
Hardaway led all scorers with 30 points and center Alonzo Mourning
added 11 and 13 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
But the Heat wilted in front of the deafening home crowd and a
Jazz defense that played best when it counted the most.
</P>
<P>
Karl Malone collected 23 points and pulled down 15 rebounds.
Russell finished with 17 points and Stockton chipped in 12 points
and eight assists for the Jazz.
</P>
<P>
In Portland, the Trail Blazers had to make use of 5-of-6 free
throws in the final 79 seconds to seal their fifth straight win 79-
72 over the Golden State Warriors, who was held scoreless in the
final three minutes.
</P>
<P>
In San Antonio, twin towers Tim Duncan and David Robinson led
the Spurs to a 112-82 rout of the Denver Nuggets while in
Cleveland, with six players in double figures the Cavaliers
pounded the Boston Celtics 113-86.
</P>
<P>
In Orlando, the Magic outplayed the Charlotte Hornets 86-78 as
the Raptors got off to a fast start and slammed Bulls 113-90, the
first win in Chicago. 
</P>
