<HEADLINE> Shoddy Commodities Threaten Leading Chinese Motorcycle Maker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Jialing Industrial Co. Ltd.,
China's number one producer of motorcycles, will take effective
measures to fight against counterfeit and shoddy motorcycles that
harm both consumers and the company.
</P>
<P>
According to He Yanqing, deputy president of the Chongqing-
based company, his business has suffered huge economic losses as
counterfeit and shoddy products are sold at half the market prices
of his company's Jialing-brand motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
He, in Shenyang, the provincial capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province, to attend a regional sales promotion meeting,
said his company has garnered one-fifth of China's motorcycle
market in terms of sales.
</P>
<P>
The vice president pledged that they will continue to cooperate
with local technical supervision departments and industrial and
commercial administrations to fight against counterfeit and shoddy
products and punish those responsible for making them. He also
complained that protectionism in some localities makes it
difficult to fight against shoddy and bogus goods. 
</P>
