<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Investment in Environment Brings High Returns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The annual reports of listed
companies on China's two stock exchanges indicate that investment
in the environmental protection industry has brought high profits.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang Environmental Protection Equipment Co. Ltd., based
in the capital of the northeastern province of Liaoning, gained
255 million yuan in income from its main business operation last
year, up 63.5 percent over 1997.
</P>
<P>
Profits from the operation jumped 68.8 percent to 130 million
yuan, with the profit rate of its main business operations
reaching 51 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Shenyang municipal government has been
rendering strong support to the company with an annual subsidy of
60 million yuan, allowing corporate profits to more than triple
since 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Chongqing Development Co. Ltd., a real estate company in
the southwestern municipality, purchased a local sewage-treatment
plant last year and generated a yearly profit of 18.5 million yuan,
which accounted for more than 31 percent of the corporation's
total profits.
</P>
<P>
The company projected this year's operational income at 35
million yuan, an increase of 60 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
China is in the process of spending 450 billion yuan on
environmental protection between 1996 and 2000, and the figure
accounts for 1.3 percent of the gross national product and 3.5
percent of the total social fix-asset investment, respectively,
for the period.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 182 billion yuan will be spent on water-treatment
facilities, 208 billion yuan on the control of air pollution, and
50 billion yuan on solid-waste treatment. This indicates bright
prospects for environment-related industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
