<HEADLINE> Shaanxi to Host Trade Fair on East-West China Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The '99 Investment and Trade Fair
for Cooperation between East and West China will be held here on
April 6-10.
</P>
<P>
Over 10,000 government officials and business people from the
country's 25 provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions, as
well as from the United States, Germany, Thailand and Spain will
participate in the fair.
</P>
<P>
The annual trade fair is jointly sponsored by the State
Economic and Trade Commission, the State Administration of
Internal Trade, the provincial governments of Shaanxi, Jiangsu,
Anhui and Sichuan, and Beijing, Tianjin and Shanghai
municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The focus will be on cooperation between the eastern and
western regions of China, expansion of domestic demand, adjustment
of economic structure, attracting investment, and commodities
exchange.
</P>
<P>
So far, the organizing committee has received 2,924 projects
via the Internet, and 15,000 people have searched cyberspace for
information about the trade. 
