<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TechWorld'99 Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 300 technology experts as
well as venture capitalists, technology developers and government
officials from China, the United States, Russia and Europe joined
their local counterparts in the TechWorld'99 which opened today.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Industrial Technology Center
Corporation (Tech Center), TechWorld'99 is an annual international
expo-conference in the Asia-Pacific region that focuses on
technology and capital.
</P>
<P>
The event was established to provide exhibitors a venue to
showcase their latest innovative products and services to
potential partners, venture capitalists and buyers.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Raymond Ch'ien, chairman of Tech Center, said the event
aims at bringing "the best people and resources together," and to
"bridge the gap between new commercially applicable technologies
developed in the region and sources of international venture
capital."
</P>
<P>
China's Vice-Minister of Science and Technology Xu Guanhua and
Chairman of Hong Kong Chief Executive's Commission on Innovation
and Technology Chang-Lin Tien were among those who officiated at
the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
With this year's theme as "Connecting Technology and Capital,"
the objective of TechWorld'99 is to facilitate deals by matching
technology providers with investors.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 matchmaking sessions have been arranged to help the
participants source capital from venture capitalists and investors.
</P>
<P>
For Hong Kong, TechWorld'99 is expected to position it as the
region's center of innovation and technology, provide
infrastructure for its industry, facilitate the collaboration
between the Silicon Valley and China, and help commercialize
research products from developers, according to organizers.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day event, leading technology experts will
conduct a series of seminars on high-tech financing and investment,
policies and regulations as well as the latest technology
development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Among the exhibitors are a 60-member delegation from Beijing
headed by Vice-Mayor Lin Wenyi and a similar delegation from South
China's Shenzhen city.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Industrial Technology Center Corporation was
incorporated in 1993 as a statutory body to stimulate the growth
of Hong Kong's high-technology industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
