<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Donates Eyes for Posthumous Collection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina has pledged her eyes for posthumous transplantation, press
reports here reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hasina, a life member of the Bangladesh Society for the Blind,
made the announcement here Tuesday while inaugurating an eye care
project, which was implemented by the Bangladesh National Council
for the Blind and funded by the Sight Savers International of
Royal Commonwealth Society for the Blind.
</P>
<P>
Arrangements had been made for treating eye patients in 504
hospitals and medicare centers in the country, while the National
Institute for Ophthalmology was carrying out research work on eye
disease and treatment, she said.
</P>
<P>
To provide essential health services to the people, the
Bangladeshi government would construct 13,500 community health
clinics, and one medicare center would be constructed for each
6,000 people to attain the objective of health for all by the year
2000, according to the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
She called upon all philanthropists and the well-to-do section
of the society to come forward in aid of the suffering humanity.
</P>
