<DOCNO> XIE19990324.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Leaders Meet on Reform, Executive Succession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The leaders of the 15-nation
European Union (EU) gathered here on Wednesday in a bid to reach a
consensus on the bloc's financial reform and EU executive body's
succession.
</P>
<P>
The most important and complicated issue at the two-day summit
is the Agenda 2000 reform package, a program of budgetary changes
aimed at checking costly farm and regional spending to prepare the
union to absorb new members from agriculture-intensive eastern and
central Europe.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, EU farm ministers, through three weeks of
complex negotiations, reached a deal on broad reform of the EU
Common Agricultural Policy (CAP), but failed to achieve radical
cuts in spending.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural support is the biggest element in the EU's annual
budget, and also the union's longest-lasting and most visible sign
of integration.
</P>
<P>
Current EU financial arrangements expire at the end of this
year. Germany, the EU's net contributor of 12.2 billion U.S.
dollars, demands a cut from the EU pay shares.
</P>
<P>
However, EU's southern member states, such as Spain, Portugal,
Greece, as well as Ireland, want to keep their gains from EU
spending at the current levels. France was also strongly opposed
to some German proposals.
</P>
<P>
Analysts hold that Germany needs to make major concessions if
the EU presidency expects achievement on Agenda 2000 at this
summit.
</P>
<P>
At the summit, the leaders will seek means to make up a new
European Commission after the 20 Commissioners resigned last week
for being accused of fraud and nepotism by an independent expert
committee set up by the European Parliament.
</P>
<P>
Now, former Italian prime minister Romano Prodi has emerged as
a clear front-runner with the backing of France, Germany, Britain,
Spain and Italy.
</P>
<P>
But German Foreign Minister Joschka Fisher said in Brussels
Monday that the 15 EU leaders would confirm a certain candidate
for the commission presidency at another summit later. The Berlin
summit mainly focuses on how to define procedures, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
