<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Conduct Air-Fare Review </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) --China will launch a nationwide
review of air-fare pricing beginning on April 1 in a bid to
maintain normal market order.
</P>
<P>
This campaign, to be carried out by the State Development
Planning Commission (SDPC) and the Civil Aviation Administration
of China (CAAC), will include all airlines and all air-ticket
booking agents.
</P>
<P>
The examination will focus on the random raising and lowering
of prices, lowering the prices by means of changing the selling
date and providing free lodging, excessive selling of tickets at
preferential prices, and boosting commissions in disguised form.
These forms of malpractice are on the rise as a result of money-
losing airlines vying for more passengers amid stiffer competition.
</P>
<P>
Those found to be in serious violation will be fined or have
their business licenses revoked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
