<HEADLINE> Sweden Appeals for Delay of World Table Tennis Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Sweden has pressed for a
postponement of the 45th world table tennis championship whose
prospect was heavily clouded for the lingering Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ulf Loennqvist, president of the Sweden Table Tennis Federation,
urged on Tuesday the International Table Tennis Federation (ITTF)
to postpone the championships in limbo and called for joint
efforts behind its appeal.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came after Germany announced they definitely
decided not send players to compete at the event, which is
scheduled from April 26 to may 9 in Belgrad, Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The world championships are the qualifying tournament for the
2000 Olympic Games so it has to go ahead in some form.
</P>
<P>
The ITTF will meet on Thursday to decide whether they will let
the championships go ahead in the Yugoslav capital if the Kosovo
crisis failed to reach a last-minute resolution.
</P>
<P>
As many as 71 countries and regions have confirmed their
entries until Monday, the deadline for registration, with some
others waiting for the final decision made by the ITTF. 
</P>
