<HEADLINE> Bulgaria to Issue New ID Documents After August 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian government has
decided to issue new personal identification documents after
August 1.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarians, aged between 14 and 18, will be the first to
receive new identity documents, which will include an ID card,
passport and driver's license, the Bulgarian official news agency
BTA reported.
</P>
<P>
The change to new identification documents will be completed
within three years, said BTA.
</P>
<P>
The new documents draw on the previous experience of 15
European countries and the United States, and meet the
requirements of the European Union, the International
Standardization Organization, the International Civil Aviation
Organization, and Interpol.
</P>
<P>
The project involves changing 17 types of national identity
documents for Bulgarian citizens, foreigners and refugees living
or visiting in the territory of Bulgaria.
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
