<HEADLINE> Venezuela to Issue New Coins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of Venezuela (
CBV) announced Tuesday new coins of 10, 20, 50, 100 and 500
Bolivars will be put into circulation on April 2.
</P>
<P>
Senior CBV official Egidio Coelho said that the coins, of
nickel plated steel and maintaining the traditional image of the
liberator Simon Bolivar, would last longer.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela's inflation rate reached 29.9 percent in 1998 and is
estimated to stand at about 20 percent this year (one U.S. dollar
is equivalent to about 580.25 Bolivars).
</P>
<P>
After the use of the new coins, Venezuela will have 8 types of
coins and 4 types of notes, which will rise to six when two new
types of notes are to be issued this summer with the par value of
20,000 and 50,000 Bolivars respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
