<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Favor Traditional Chinese Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Border trade has boosted the
export of traditional Chinese medicine to Vietnam in recent years,
the International Business Daily reported yesterday.
</P>
<P>
China now exports a large amount of traditional Chinese
medicine and some 1,000 tons of medicinal materials annually to
its neighbor through the border province of Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
China is expected to add these exports to the list of normal
trade within this year, according to the paper. Vietnam already
considers this trade to be normal, and collects a nine percent
tariff on patent medicines and five percent on imports of
medicinal materials.
</P>
<P>
These medicines are warmly welcomed in south Vietnam where 1.2
million Chinese-Vietnamese live.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's International Medicine Fair, which falls in March,
has been a major channel through which Chinese medicine producers
have been able to export their products to this market, according
to the paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
