<HEADLINE> Albania Prepares for Emergency Following NATO Strike on Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Albania is preparing for any
possible emergency following NATO military action against
Yugoslavia, Albanian Foreign Minister Paskal Milo said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came as Albania's first response to the
imminent strike on Yugoslavia authorized by NATO Secretary-General
Javier Solana Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government convened an urgent session on Solana's
authoritative order and revised its security measures adopted
recently to deal with possible emergency brought by fighting and
to defend Albania's sovereignty and territorial integrity, Milo
said.
</P>
<P>
In his letter to Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli Majko, Solana
pledged to guarantee the country's territorial integrity and
sovereignty, Milo added, calling on the people to unite together
and to keep confidence and calm.
</P>
<P>
Albania has recently mobilized ground troops and military
equipment to its northern border with Kosovo for possible NATO
strikes. The government also urged to strengthen air defense
system in the capital and northern cities and to store medicine
and medical supplies for battle use.  
</P>
