<HEADLINE> Northeast Auto City, Also Best Tourist Destination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Changchun, the provincial
capital of northeast China's Jilin Province, was recently
confirmed as one of China's best tourist cities by the China
National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
Located at the center of the northeastern plain, Changchun is
also the place where China's automotive industry emerged in the
1950s.
</P>
<P>
Featuring convenient transport, Changchun abounds in tourist
resources with a good environment and a forested area covering
nearly 40 percent of the city.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the city has 23 star-rated hotels,
including two five-star ones, and has 18 travel agencies, of which
11 are authorized to handle overseas tourists. Last year, the city
raked in more than 1.2 billion yuan from tourism.
</P>
<P>
To improve tourism services, the National Tourism
Administration initiated a program selecting the best tourist
cities in 1996. By last year, 54 Chinese cities had been given the
title of "best Chinese tourist cities."  
</P>
