<HEADLINE> Cuba Sentences Salvadoran Terrorist to Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, March 23 (Xinhua)-- A Cuban court has passed a death
sentence on a Salvadoran man who confessed to a series of hotel
bombings.
</P>
<P>
Under Cuban law, the death sentence of Raul Ernesto Cruz Leon
will be immediately appealed to the Supreme Court, the Communist
Party daily Granma said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The death sentence comes amid a general tightening of security
by the Cuban government, which in recent months has said it feels
under growing attacks by the U.S. government, violent exiles in
Miami, and political dissidents on the island.
</P>
<P>
During Cruz Leon's trial, prosecutors said that heads of the
Miami-based Cuban-American National Foundation recruited and paid
Cruz Leon to plant bombs at six tourist sites. The bombings have
killed an Italian and injured 11 others, including seven
foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Cruz Leon was allegedly paid 4,500 U.S. dollars for each
bombing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
