<HEADLINE> Sampras Loses to Krajicek after Return to N0.1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras was awakened from
the rejoicing of reclaiming the world number one ranking as he was
frustrated Tuesday by nemesis Richard Krajicek of the Netherlands
in the quarter-finals of the Lipton tennis championships.
</P>
<P>
The seventh-seeded Krajicek, took his sixth career victory in
eight matches against the American with a 6-2 , 7-6(8-6) quarter-
final win with his hard service and big shots.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who ensured his return to the men's throne with a
fourth round win over Spaniard Albert Costa on Monday, has not
reached a final in his four tournaments this year with a record of
7-3.
</P>
<P>
In women's fourth-round action, the former women's No.1 Steffi
Graf of Germany extended her winning streak at Lipton to 21
consecutive matches by beating Belarus' Natasha Zvereva 6-2, 6-4
in the fourth round.
</P>
<P>
Also moving to the quarter-finals was top-seeded Swiss teen
star Martina Hingis, who ended 19-year-old German qualifier
Marlene Weingartner's surprising run with a 6-0, 6-2 victory.
</P>
<P>
South African Amanda Coetzer, seeded ninth, advanced 6-1, 4-2
over eighth seed Mary Pierce of France who retired with a right
ankle injury while Wimbledon champion Jana Novotna of the Czech
Republic, the fourth seed, scored a 6-3, 2-6, 6-4 win over 12th-
seeded Swiss Patty Schnyder. 
</P>
