<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico to Attend OPEC Summit in Vienna as Observer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Mexico is to attend as an
observer the 107th OPEC meeting in Vienna on Wednesday, where
member countries are expected to ratify the proposed cutback of 2.
5 million barrels per day (bpd).
</P>
<P>
A communique from the Mexican Energy Ministry said that Mexico
is to attend this meeting with the aim of participating actively
in their joint effort of oil-producing countries to end the
uncertainty provoked by the instability of the oil prices.
</P>
<P>
On March 12, oil ministers of Saudi Arabia, Iran, Algeria,
Venezuela and Mexico agreed in the Hague to reduce by 2.5 million
bpd in the oil production from April 1.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the producing countries reduced oil production by 3.1
million bpd, a measure which stopped the fall in international
prices which fell to the lowest level in 22 years.
</P>
<P>
It said that the OPEC secretariat invited Mexico as an observer
and as an active participant, in the effort to avoid new falls in
the international market prices.
</P>
<P>
With the participation in the OPEC summit, Mexico's delegation
will request, in the name of the Mexican government, OPEC members
to strengthen their cooperation and stabilize the international
petroleum market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
