<HEADLINE> EDS-Updates With More Details U.S. Senate Votes to Approve Airstrikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On a vote of 58 to 41, the Senate gave its blessings to an air
campaign ordered earlier in the day by NATO, which appeared to be
imminent.
</P>
<P>
"The case of inaction is unacceptable to the world," said
Senate Armed Services Committee Chairman John Warner.
</P>
<P>
The final vote, however, was hardly an overwhelming show of
support. Thirty-eight Republicans and three Democrats opposed the
resolution.
</P>
<P>
Told earlier in the day by Clinton that strikes against Serbian
targets would proceed with or without congressional support,
Senate leaders quickly crafted a bipartisan resolution of support
and shelved earlier plans to call for a vote on whether to block
funds for such an operation.
</P>
<P>
