<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pau Defeats Holders Bologna in Basketball Euroleague </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 23 (Xinhua) -- French champions Pau-Orthez
defeated titleholders Kinder Bologna of Italy 67-59 in the first
leg of their basketball Euroleague quarter-final on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
American Emmanual Davis, his team's best scorer on 15 points,
was again Pau's key player as he scored twice to hand them a 45-38
lead shortly after the break.
</P>
<P>
In the first half, veteran American Ronnie Smith kept Pau
afloat with 11 points before leaving his place to Davis. Bologna
had given its rivals a lot of problems at first, leading 21-13 in
the 10th minute.
</P>
<P>
But Pau caught up on the break thanks to a three-pointer by
Davis, which opened the floodgates for Pau in the second half.
</P>
</TEXT>
