<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Giger Replaces Margreiter as Austrian Alpine Skiing Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Toni Giger will replace Werner
Margreiter as head coach of the Austrian men's Alpine skiing team,
officials said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Federation president Peter Schroecksnadel said Margreiter would
remain with the team in other functions while Karl Frehsner would
continue coaching the equally successful women's squad.
</P>
<P>
Giger, under Margreiter, coached the men's super-G and giant
slalom squads, leading Hermann Maier to two world and two Olympic
gold medals as well as the 1998 overall World Cup title within 12
months.
</P>
<P>
Austria's ski jumping coach, Mika Kojonkowski, will leave the
team to become head coach in his home country, Finland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
