<HEADLINE> Brazil Stocks Fall Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on the Sao Paulo
exchange, the largest in Latin America, closed down for a second
straight day Tuesday, at 10,416 points against 10,527 Monday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover reached some 226 million dollars, higher than
Monday's 166 million dollars but much lower than last weekend's
285 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In Rio de Janeir, stocks closed at 34,354 points against 34,576
points on Monday, a fall of 0.6 percent. The turnover was 15.652
million dollars, compared with 13,892 million dollars on Monday.
</P>
</TEXT>
