<HEADLINE> Hainan to Host International Coconut Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 24 (Xinhua) -- South China's Hainan Province is
to host the eighth international coconut festival from April 6 to
20 in its capital Haikou and other three major cities.
</P>
<P>
The festival will include nearly one hundred activities
featuring ecological tourism, afforestation, trade fairs, ethnic
art and a gala of folk customs.
</P>
<P>
The annual festival was first launched in 1992 and has since
lured millions of domestic and overseas tourists and business
people to this island province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
