<HEADLINE> NBA Players McGrady and Henderson Fined </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Toronto Raptors forward Tracy
McGrady and Atlanta Hawks forward Alan Henderson were fined $3,500
each by the NBA on Tuesday for separate incidents the past three
days.
</P>
<P>
McGrady hit New Jersey Nets forward Jamie Feick in the head
with a flagrant forearm in the second quarter of Monday's 106-87
road loss. On Saturday, Henderson threw a basketball into the
stands during the third quarter of an 83-77 home loss to the
Milwaukee Bucks.
</P>
<P>
Neither player was suspended.
</P>
<P>
19-year-old McGrady is averaging 8.9 points and 5.9 assists for
the surprising Raptors, who had a five-game winning streak snapped
Monday.
</P>
<P>
In his fourth season out of Indiana, Henderson is second on the
Hawks with 13.0 points and 7.0 rebounds. 
</P>
