<HEADLINE> Zhejiang's Industry Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The industrial sector of east
China's Zhejiang Province has started 1999 on a strong note,
official figures show.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises and non-state firms with annual sales
of more than five million yuan each generated a total of 66.72
billion yuan in output value in the first two months of this year,
up 18.9 percent over the same period of last year. The growth rate
is 7.3 percentage points higher than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises reported 4.78 billion yuan in profits and taxes
in January and February, a year-on-year jump of 36.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's two-month exports rose 15.2 percent to 1.53 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The improved performance of the industrial enterprises as a
whole in this economically developed province is attributed to the
central government policies to increase domestic demand, which
help accelerate structural reform in the industrial sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
