<DOCNO> XIE19990324.0315 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Council of Ministers Discusses Budget Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The 69th Ordinary Session of
the Council of Ministers of the Organization of African Unity
(OAU) discussed extensively Tuesday and Monday the budgetary,
administrative and social affairs of the organization.
</P>
<P>
Briefing journalists here, OAU Spokesman Ibrahim Dagash said
the meeting, after making some amendments, has accepted a report
on the OAU Secretariat' s structural reform.
</P>
<P>
Dagash said 19 million U.S. dollars is needed for the
implementation of the structural reform of the OAU.
</P>
<P>
He said the reform is aimed at adjusting the secretariat's
structure and adopting it to the new realities and modern methods
of work.
</P>
<P>
He said the report will be submitted for approval to the OAU
Summit to be held in Algeria in the coming June.
</P>
<P>
Although member countries of the OAU are paying their dues
appropriately, the organization has continued to impose embargoes
on eight African countries which failed to pay their arrears to
it, according to the OAU Spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The two-day 69th Session of the Council of Ministers is
expected to close here tonight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
