Primakov abruptly postponed a planned trip to Washington Tuesday
after he was briefed by U.S. Vice President Al Gore on
unsuccessful diplomatic efforts to resolve the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Russia has steadfastly opposed threatened NATO airstrikes
against Serb targets in the province.
</P>
<P>
"After discussing the worsening situation in Kosovo, Prime
Minister Primakov decided to return to Moscow," Gore said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
During a refueling stop in Shannon, Ireland, before the trip
was postponed, Primakov made clear his country's opposition to a
NATO attack.
