<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Minister Satisfied with Egypt Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Italian Minister of Industry and
Energy Pierluigi Bersani on Sunday expressed satisfaction with his
two-day visit in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters before wrapping up his trip, Bersani
termed his talks with Egypt's ministers of electricity, petroleum
and industry as "very constructive."
</P>
<P>
The talks reviewed means of boosting Egyptian-Italian relations
in all fields, Bersani said.
</P>
<P>
The visit is a continuation of talks initiated during Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak's recent visit to Italy, the Italian
officials underlined. Mubarak paid a two-day visit to Italy on
February 22-23.
</P>
<P>
He added that his visit reflects Italy's keenness on setting up
economic projects in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Bersani said that he has invited Egypt's ministers of energy,
petroleum and industry to visit Rome to continue talks pertaining
to fostering bilateral cooperation in all fields.
</P>
<P>
The two sides earlier signed a technical cooperation protocol
in the electricity and energy areas, under which a joint committee
will be formed, comprising representatives from the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The committee is due to convene twice a year in Rome and Cairo
to work out action plans to overcome obstacles to investment in
joint ventures in the fields of energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
