<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Arrives in Milan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MILAN, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
arrived here Tuesday afternoon from Rome to continue his state
visit to Italy.
</P>
<P>
Italian Minister of Foreign Trade Piero Fassino accompanied
Jiang to Milan.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Rome, Jiang held talks with his Italian
counterpart, Oscar Luigi Scalfaro, met with Italian Prime Minister
Massimo D'alema, parliament leaders, leaders of international
organizations in Rome and entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
Those of Jiang's entourage who boarded the same plane are: his
wife Wang Yeping, Vice Premier Qian Qichen and his wife Zhou
Hanqiong, Minister in Charge of the State Development Commission
Zeng Peiyan, Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Shi Guangsheng, Director of the Policy Research Office of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Teng
Wensheng, China's Ambassador to Italy Wu Minglian and his wife,
Vice Foreign Minister Wang Yingfan, Deputy Director of the General
Office of the CPC Central Committee You Xigui and Director of the
President's Office Jia Ting'an. 
</P>
</TEXT>
