<HEADLINE> Clinton Prepares Americans for War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- President Bill Clinton on
Tuesday prepared the American people for an airstrike against
Yugoslav targets, acknowledging U.S. forces would be put at risk.
</P>
<P>
"I want to level with you," Clinton said in a speech to a union
group and the American public at large. "This is like any other
military action. There are risks in it."
</P>
<P>
"We have to take a stand now," he said. "if we don't do it now,
we will have to do it later."
</P>
<P>
Clinton warned Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic that NATO
is "united and prepared" to carry out strikes against Serb
targets.
</P>
<P>
He said if Milosevic is not willing to make peace in Kosovo,
then the United States and its NATO allies are willing to limit
his ability to make war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
